<document xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
          xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/xdoc-2.0.xsd">

    <properties>
        <title>maven-t7-plugin</title>
    </properties>
    
    
    <body>
        <div class="hero-unit">
            <p>
                <h1>maven-t7-plugin</h1>
            </p>
            <p>It's so easy to run Tomcat 7 (or 6 if you want) in your Maven project. Just add corresponding 
                <em>groupId</em>, 
                <em>artifactId</em> and 
                <em>version</em> to your pom.xml.
            </p>
            <pre>&lt;plugin&gt;
    &lt;groupId>com.googlecode.t7mp&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId>maven-t7-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version>0.9.10.M8&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
            </pre>
            <p>Start your build as usual with the following goal:
                <br/>
                <pre>mvn t7:run</pre>
            </p>
            <p>That's it.</p>
        </div>
    </body>
</document>